# Patterns that trigger an "inline code execution detected" ask. The hook
# prefers reviewable script files over arbitrary code on the command line.
#
# Format: <command> <flag1> [<flag2> ...]
# Each line compiles into a regex of the form
#   \b<command>\s+(?:--?[\w-]+\s+)*(?:<flag1>|<flag2>|...)\b
# so intermediate flags are allowed (e.g. `node -i -e "..."` still matches).
# The ask reason uses "<command> <flag1>" as the human-readable name.
#
# If this file is missing or empty, the inline-exec check does NOT fire and
# `node -e ...` / `python -c ...` etc. pass without prompting.

node -e -p --eval --print
bun -e
python -c
python3 -c
ruby -e
perl -e
deno eval
